#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:5
msgid "Fields Configuration"
msgstr "Configuration des champs"

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:8
msgid "Mandatory fields and access rights"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:10
msgid ""
"When you create or edit a member, some fields are mandatory. Default "
"configuration may not suit your needs, but you can configure some elements "
"easily ;)"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:12
msgid ""
"From the `Configuration`, `Core fields` menu, you will get access to all "
"fields available for members, and choose for each one if it is mandatory or "
"not, as well as associated access rights:"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:14
msgid "`inaccessible` will make the field inaccessible for everyone,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:15
msgid ""
"`administrator` will make the field readable and writeable for "
"administrators only,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:16
msgid ""
"`staff members` will make the field readable and writable for staff members "
"and administrators,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:17
msgid ""
"`groups managers` will make the field readable and writable for groups "
"managers on the memebrs of groups they own, and for staff memebrs and "
"administrators,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:18
msgid ""
"`read/write` will make the field readable and writeable for member, groups "
"managers, staff members and administrators,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:19
msgid ""
"`read only` will make the field read only for the members, but writable for "
"groups managers, staff members and administrators."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:27
msgid "Dynamic fields"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:29
msgid ""
"Galette comes per default with many fields for members, contributions and "
"transactions. Some of them will be useless, but you may need fields that "
"does not exists..."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:31
msgid ""
"In this case, that is quite simple : just add a new dynamic field with a "
"label, define if it is mandatory or not, and that's all : Galette will "
"handle them automatically, just show the result ;)"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:33
msgid "There are several types of dynamic fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:35
msgid "`separator`: just a label, like a part title,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:36
msgid "`free text`: multiline text area,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:37
msgid "`single line`: one line text,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:38
msgid "`choice`: a dropdown list,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:39
msgid "`date`: a date field with a selector,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:40
msgid "`boolean`: a checkbox,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:41
msgid "`file`: add files."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:43
msgid "While creating a new field (or editing an existing one); you also can:"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:45
msgid "mark it as required,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:46
msgid "define access rights, tha same as for core fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:53
msgid ""
"Some field types like separators, dates and booleans, does not need any "
"extra information; for others:"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:55
msgid "`free text`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:57
msgid "`width`: define number of columns,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:58
msgid "`height`: define number of rows."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:60
msgid "`single line`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:62
msgid "`width`: field width,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:63
msgid "`size`: number of characters,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:64
msgid "`repeat`: number of possible ocurences."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:66
msgid "`choice`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:68
msgid "`values`: possible values for the dropdown."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:70
msgid "`file`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:72
msgid ""
"`size`: maximum file size, in Kio (this size is limited to the one for the "
"PHP configuration)."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:75
msgid "Labels translation"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:77
msgid ""
"Galette handle several languages, but when you add a new dynamic field, "
"there is only one value possible. Galette proposes an interface to translate"
" those labels in each available language."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:79
msgid "Note that each new label will be added with current Galette lang."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:82
msgid "Emails contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:84
msgid ""
"Depending on your configuration (see preferences), administrative emails "
"cans be sent to users and/or administrators, when you add a new member or a "
"new contribution, or from the lost password feature for example."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:86
msgid "Defaults are provided, but you can change them."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:88
msgid ""
"It is important to note that those textes contain variables - of the "
"``{VARIABLE}`` form - that will be replaced automatically on sending. Be "
"carefull to not forget any of those, that could cause sending issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:95
msgid "An email will be send to member when:"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:97
msgid "he self subscribes. This mail contains authentication informations,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:98
msgid ""
"his card is added or edited by someone else (if the corresponding box is "
"checked),"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:99
msgid "he uses lost password feature,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:100
msgid ""
"a new contribution is attache to his account (if the corresponding box is "
"checked)."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:102
msgid "An email will be send to administrators when:"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:104
msgid "a new member is added or self subscribes,"
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:105
msgid "a new contribution is attached to his account."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:107
msgid ""
"Of course, emails will be sent ony if Galette configuration allows it (and "
"the setup is correct). Sending messages to administrators is configured "
"globally from the preferences, while sending emails to members is "
"conditionned on a checkbox from the user interface, excepting for self "
"subscription messages that will always be send."
msgstr ""

#: ../usermanual/configuration.rst:109
msgid ""
"Several variables - automatically replaced on sending - are available for "
"both subject and contents. Some of them may be used in all messages, but "
"others will be only on some conditions. Refer to the inline help on Galette "
"interface to know more."
msgstr ""
